title: For Sale:  20" Heavy Barrel AR-15 Upper Superior Arms, No BCG/CH
postcontent:
Hey guys,
  I'm selling my 20 inch heavy barrel Superior Arms upper. This is an extremely accurate and very smooth shooting upper. The rifle length gas system is renowned for offering .22 LR levels of recoil, and this upper is no different. Recoil is almost nil. I've only shot about 400 rounds through this guy, so it still has tons of life left in it. The heavy profile barrel does make the gun heavier, but I've easily done 1.5 inch groups at 100 yards. A better shooter than me could do even tighter groups.

  This upper has all the goodies: Forward assist, dust cover, M4 feed ramps, 20 inch heavy barrel, rifle length gas system, Magpul MOE rifle handguard, standard M4 front sight block, and I'm including an M16/M4 carry handle rear sight as well. It adds an authentic look to the rifle and normally those alone are 80 dollars. Does not come with a bolt carrier group or charging handle, but if you have an AR, then you've already got those parts on hand.

  For this quality upper, I'm only asking 300 dollars. Most new 20 inch uppers online cost at least 450 dollars and I would wager aren't as nice as what Superior Arms produces. For more detailed pictures, please shoot me an email. Thank you for looking and have a great day.

title: Want To Buy:  Percussion Musket/Rifled-Musket, Civil War Re-enactment Or Others
postcontent:
Hello,


   Looking for a reproduction musket or rifled-musket. Ideally, I'd like to get an 1861 Springfield Rifled-Musket in .58, with bayonet, but a lot of people out there seem to think this gun is worth more used than new. $700 is my upper limit on value, and while I don't have a ton of cash on hand, I DO have an absolute heaven of man-goods to trade for the gun:

-MRE's
-Tactical Gear
-Military Surplus
-Paintball Guns/Gear
-Airsoft Guns/Gear
-Crossbows/Bows/Hunting Gear
-Outdoors Gear
-Collectibles
-Warhammer
-Medieval weapons(not toys or replicas, the real deal reproduction); swords, spears, lances, axes, shields, chainmail, armor, you name it.
-SCA gear
-Black Powder Supplies
-Black Powder Firearms
-Tasers(Many types)
-Body Armor(Class I through IV)
-Helmets, Military or Airsoft
-Oakley ballistic glasses
-Ammunition, most common calibers(used up my 9mm and .22LR, sorry)




I will consider any reproduction that has a percussion or flintlock system(sorry matchlockers, one of you is plenty enough trouble for me), from any era in any caliber. Got a French musket designed 1752? Awesome, I'll check it out. Priority will be given to 1861 Springfields, but other than that it's fair game. I'd also consider modern repro's like Hawkens and the like, but I'm really looking for the military models. If it doesn't fit a bayonet, I'm probably not going to buy it.

--HAVING A BAYONET WITH YOUR GUN IS A HUGE PLUS--


I don't really need slings or frogs, etc. The rifle and a bayonet are my goals; anything beyond that is just fluff that I may or may not be interested in. A good leather sling would be nice, provided it's historically accurate.


I'm looking primarily for rust. So long as it doesn't have rust, I don't really care if you're a horrible gun owner and you've used the stock as a hammer the past six months. In fact, I'd prefer a "beater" simply so I don't have to buy new. The worst-case scenario here folks is; I go to Cabela's and place an order for a brand new one, at a cost of $800. I'd really rather avoid that and buy someone's unwanted gun off of them.

postcontent: Other 215S, 208S potentially available: indicte desired price range with inquiry.  Starting at $1800, up to $3400.  Shipping Available.  End version of the legendary 208/International, the S-model offers a 2 stage trigger with adjustable trigger position. The basic sight system, and interchangeable barrel weights with rail that can accept an optical sight mount were retained.  The model offered is a commemorative version. Same as the other S models, but with a better finish, and gold lettering. The Morini grip is original to the gun, and has been modified slightly to correct the problems with the stock Morini grip shelf.  Mechanically PERFECT.Armslist does not always succeed inforwarding inquiries.  Please see my 208 listing, or the images of the GSP listing for other contact routes.The S model uses a trigger system modified from the older 208, but similar to the 215 and the later 208 guns. These changes were made to reduce production cost. Trigger quality was neither improved nor decreased.Like the S&W41, the 208 and the S model evolved from the Walther Olympia of the 1930s, which itself was an adaptation of the Reising Target Pistol. After an unsuccessful adaptation by Hammerli following WWII as the Hammerli Walther Olympia, the International saw the gun revised extensive with a far superior result.  The 208, and by pass-through of the inheritance, is, in essence, the ultimate S&W41 that Smith and Wesson never made.The barrel is a solid unit with the frame, with superb (close to 0.5 MOA) accuracy resulting. The trigger is excellent for consistency, and readily adjustable from about 400 gms to about 3000. In addition to having a "fine" adjustment, this gun offers a coarse adjustment system for rapid adjustment from heavy to light pull weights.The S model is slightly LESS accurate than the older 208 guns, but the difference is very difficult to detect, and many prefer the S due to the adjustable trigger position and 2 stage option.Gun weight can be adjusted by change in barrel weights (0-240 gm available). location: Clarksville, Tiny town and trenton, Clarksville, Tennessee
postcontent: ARAK-21® Features Components of the ARAK-21® Upper Receiver: The ARAK-21® is a gas piston actuated, complete upper receiver assembly designed to seamlessly interface with the standard AR-15 platform. The total extent of the interface is simply the take down pin, and the pivot pin. The new ARAK-21® upper receiver offers you all its features with no change to your current lower receiver and can be installed in less than one minute with no tools. The BAU is comprised of the barrel, gas block, muzzle brake, gas piston, gas adjuster, and barrel trunnion. The only removable part of this assembly is the gas adjuster knob. The gas adjuster knob has 4 settings. Three of the settings allow different gas flows for optimum operation, and one setting blocks the gas flow for a single shot operation. The upper receiver includes the charging block, standard charging handle, lower forearm with screws, three aluminum full length picatinny rails, three insulating shims, bolt carrier assembly, lower recoil lug with spring guide rod, and dual recoil spring system. Along with your new ARAK-21® upper receiver you will receive your owners manual, and two allen wrenches that will fit the screws that attach the lower forearm, and the front picatinny rails. Due to the unique and innovative features of the ARAK-21® upper receiver, there are very few parts that are interchangeable with a standard AR-15. The firing pin, extractor spring, and ejector spring are the only parts that are standard and interchangeable with an AR-15 upper receiver. Other features include: The upper receiver is fully machined from an aircraft grade 6061-T6 aluminum billet in a one piece design that incorporates a full length picatinny rail (Mil-STD-1913) on the top and three additional rails on the muzzle end of the receiver, making it a full M4 style quad rail upper. The top picatinny rail is laser engraved for optic placement. There are also half-length picatinny rails available.12 ½” length BAU is available in 5.56, heavy profile. 16” and 20” length BAU’s are available in both the 5.56 and 300 BLK. There are two profiles to choose from, medium and heavy. BAU’s can be interchanged in less than 3 minutes by removing the (6) captive allen screws on the bottom rail using the enclosed allen wrench. Long stroke variable setting gas piston system. There are three options for gas flow, and one for no gas flow. This allows for single shot operation. There is also a clean out port for the gas block between the gas cylinder, and the bolt. Self-contained firing pin retention system enclosed in a rectangular bolt carrier that no longer requires a cotter pin.Bolted in hardened steel rail system for the bolt carrier to ride on. This allows a metal on metal wear surface for better wear characteristics and a much smoother operation.The ARAK-21® system allows for a folding stock to be added, as our recoil system does not extend beyond the upper receiver to fully operate. This eliminates the noise and feel of the buffer tube cycling back and forth. ARAK-21 Upper Receiver Includes: ARAK-21 Upper (As Ordered)Shipping BoxManualBAU Removal ToolsMagazine Marker Bands (300 BLK & 7.62x39, if ordered)Bolt(s) & Firing Pin(s) for Ordered CalibersRecoil Spring(s) for Ordered Calibers Faxon Technical. Weight: The complete rifle weighs in less than 7 lbs, with no magazine or accessories. The standard ARAK-21 upper receiver with a 16" medium barrel weights in at 5.5 lbs. Pencil barrels remove .3 lbs and heavy barrels increase the weight .3 lbs. Uppers equipped with 12.5" medium barrels weigh approximately 5 lbs. Heavy 20" barrels increase the base weight approximately .5 lbs. 300 BLK Functionality: The 300 AAC BlackOut barrels are designed to function reliably with supersonic ammunition stand-alone and subsonic ammunition when used with suppressor. The 12.5" barrel may not be functional with all ammunition. It will be important for the end-user to establish the best performing ammunition. Note: The use of a suppressor will improve the function and reliability of the 12.5" 300 AAC Blackout ARAK-21® barrel.
